# orchestratorX (DEPRECATED)

**Status**: DEPRECATED as of 2026-06-10

**Reason**: orchestratorX functionality has been merged into the Main Claude Agent. The Main Agent now acts as the orchestrator directly, maintaining long-term memory across conversations.

**Migration**: 
- All orchestration logic now in `CLAUDE.md`
- Workflow definitions remain in `.claude/skills/orchestrator-playbook/`
- Main Agent directly executes Mode A/B/C workflows
- Main Agent directly calls coderX/evaluatorX as sub-agents

**Historical Purpose**: 
This file previously defined orchestratorX as a sub-agent responsible for workflow orchestration. However, this architecture caused context loss between conversation turns, as sub-agents start fresh sessions each time.

**Reference Only**: Keep this file for historical reference but do NOT use `Agent(orchestratorX)` in any new implementations.
